                                Presents
                            ADI FRENCH 14/15

                   Typed and Edited by DIT 13-06-1994

                                   ADI
                               French 14/15

 ADI French 14/15 has been written for pupils in the fourth year of their
senior education. This application conforms to six Areas of Experience
within the National Curriculum (see below). It is composed of six
chapters, which take several themes (Police File, Geography, Occupations,
Lost Property, Pocket money and Holidays). Textural material is used
throughout these chapters and reflects the themes of the chapters.
Students will be able to work through this application in the confidence
that they will be learning under ADI's watchful eye. He will provide them
with help and advice when they need it.

              ADI French 14/15 and the National Curriculum

 How ADI French 14/15 relates to the National Curriculum Areas of
Experience - Attainment Target 3 (Reading) & 4 (Writing):

 Area A:  Everyday Activities (food, drink, leisure & sports)
 Area C: The World Around Us (Natural world, home town)
 Area D: The World of Education, Training & Work
 Area E: The World of Communications (I.T.)
 Area F: The International World
 Area G: the World of Imagination & Creativity

 G.C.S.E. TOPIC AREAS

 * Money
 * Geographical Surroundings
 * Holidays
 * Services
 * Travel & Transport
 * Education & Future Careers

